\", \"from\": 3926, \"to\": 3943}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic sports\", \"from\": 3947, \"to\": 3961}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She organized the first Women's Olympic Games in Paris in 1922, bringing together five countries and 77 athletes.\", \"from\": 3967, \"to\": 4080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4016, \"end\": 4021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8650994553234893e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first Women's Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3981, \"to\": 4012}, {\"ngram\": \"five countries\", \"from\": 4049, \"to\": 4063}, {\"ngram\": \"77 athletes\", \"from\": 4068, \"to\": 4079}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although Milliat \\\"died in obscurity\\\" in 1957, her \\\"legacy endures today, with the Paris 2024 Games highlighting gender equality in sports, largely thanks to her visionary efforts,\\\" says the photo caption.\", \"from\": 4082, \"to\": 4286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Milliat\", \"from\": 4091, \"to\": 4098}, {\"ngram\": \"obscurity\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4117}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Games\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4180}, {\"ngram\": \"gender equality\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4209}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4213, \"to\": 4219}, {\"ngram\": \"her visionary efforts\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4260}, {\"ngram\": \"the photo caption\", \"from\": 4268, \"to\": 4285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, the exhibition spotlights the contributions of disabled athletes such as Ryadh Sallem, who was born without arms or legs, a victim of the Thalidomide medication that was prescribed to pregnant women in the 1950s and Sixties and caused deformities in children.\", \"from\": 4288, \"to\": 4558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4437, \"end\": 4448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thalidomide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"T